    <item>
      <title>Example Paper Note</title>
      <link>/paper-notes/example_note/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 02 May 2026 15:26:03 +0900</pubDate>
      <guid>/paper-notes/example_note/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;preventing-network-bottlenecks&#34;&gt;Preventing Network Bottlenecks:&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;accelerating-datacenter-services-with-hotspot-aware&#34;&gt;Accelerating Datacenter Services with Hotspot-Aware&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;placement-for-compute-and-storage&#34;&gt;Placement for Compute and Storage&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;/ 什么是hotspot&#xA;Datacenter network hotspots, defined as links with persistently high utilization, can lead to performance bottlenecks.&#xA;网络里的局部热点拥塞点，也就是某一小块网络资源长期或频繁地特别忙，利用率很高，因而拖慢经过它的流量。&#xA;类似地图，红色的部分就是拥挤严重的路段&#xA;不过，在这里指的是，经常容易堵、并且会持续一段时间的路段&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
